page.title: 04THE MANOR HOUSE,FENSTANTON
page.content:
{The Manor House,Chequers Street was built in 1550.The most famous person that lived there was{Lancelot {(Capability) Brown,}who moved into the Manor in 1767. Lord Northampton gave Capability Brown the Manor House because he owed him Â£12,000. { Capabilty said,'If you give me {the Manor of Fenstanton,you don't have {to pay Â£12,000' { }Dorothy Stroud wrote a book on Capability Brown.{ { He died in 1783. The Browns had {the Manor until 1869.} {Mr.& Mrs. Robbins}have owned the house for 20 years.They like living there and have refused all offers to sell.The Manor House has 10 rooms. In the garden is a high water table and a filled in well.
